\begin{abstract}
We present the Onu-Ma'at Synthesis, a framework that unifies atomic-scale emotional coherence with cosmological dynamics using a log-linear gauge field—the \textbf{Onu Gauge}. The theory is parameterized by three constants—Lule's ($V_0$), Zayyay's ($\Xi$), and the Leakage Coefficient ($k$). We introduce the \textbf{Onu Breathing Operator} ($\OnuOp$), a scale-localized dynamic projector that enforces boundary contact between vacuum and ultra-density limits. This operator upgrades the pressure tensor to a "Breathing Torus" topology, stabilizing microscopic octanodal confinement and introducing time-dependent modulation to the Galactic Law. We conclude with an incontrovertible test for the Zayyay Floor ($\Xi$) in gravitational wave data.
\end{abstract}

